The controlling expression can be invariant when the macro expands to a compile-time constant. For example, if threading support is disabled (e.g. MHD_USE_THREADS not defined) the macro MHD_D_IS_USING_THREAD_PER_CONN_(daemon) may be defined to 0 (or 1) regardless of the runtime 'daemon' argument, making the if (MHD_D_IS_USING_THREAD_PER_CONN_(daemon)) an invariant controlling expression (if (0) or if (1)). In that compilation/configuration case Rule 14.3 is violated.
